JOHANNESBURG - The National Prosecuting Authority will open three cases related to the murder of anti-apartheid activist Ahmed Timol. A former security police officer could be facing perjury charges. READ: Timol inquest: Calls for repercussions The NPA is set to investigate Timol's death and the subsequent attempt to cover it up. It's been 46 years since he died in police custody. A recent inquest found that Timol was murdered. This is against the apartheid police's original report that he'd committed suicide. eNCA